My original draft for this article actually did that! The first version was going heavier on the  concept, and the implication that you (the reader) are the one in the simulation. Had hidden messages and all sorts, from a doomsday group that wanted to wake up all the candidates prematurely and end the universe.

At the end, one would attempt to interact with you through a terminal interface and you could respond to it. However, regardless of your response, the Foundation would cut you off and redirect you to another page, falsely claiming there was a  on the page and so it had been deleted.

You can find that original version here if you're curious: http://firedawnfolder.wikidot.com/fragment:scp-wakeup-0

If you go to the bottom, open the last collapsible (+ Open /0/union.txt) and click one of the buttons at the bottom, it'll do the cut-out thing you expected!







